# SnapTidy Project Rules

## Safety
- NEVER delete files — only move them
- NEVER enter .photoslibrary or .photolibrary directories
- Always get user confirmation before applying move plans
- Log all file operations to CSV audit trail

## Code Style
- Python 3.9+, PEP 8, 4-space indent
- CLI scripts use argparse with --input/--output flags
- All data exchange via CSV (UTF-8 with BOM)
- No heavy dependencies (no pandas/numpy)

## Pipeline
1. scan_photos.py → photo_index.csv
2. find_exact_duplicates.py → duplicates.csv
3. generate_move_plan.py → move_plan.csv
4. apply_move_plan.py → move_log.csv (requires user confirmation)

## Testing
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python3 scripts/scan_photos.py --input /path/to/photos --output ./photo_index.csv
```
